+modbus_set_broadcasts(3)
+===================
+
+
+NAME
+----
+modbus_set_broadcasts - enable or disable broadcasts in the context.
+
+
+SYNOPSIS
+--------
+*int modbus_set_broadcasts(modbus_t *'ctx', int 'enable');*
+
+
+DESCRIPTION
+-----------
+The *modbus_set_broadcasts()* function shall enable or disable broadcasts for the context
+
+The broadcast address is `MODBUS_BROADCAST_ADDRESS`. This special value must be set before sending
+broadcast messages/requests. When enabled, the context will not expect a response from the slave.
+The behavior is oposite when disabled, the context will expect a response from the slave even when slave ID
+is set to `MODBUS_BROADCAST_ADDRESS`.
+
+RETURN VALUE
+------------
+There is no return values.
+
+
+ERRORS
+------
+There is no specific error for this function,
+but it may fail if the context is not properly initialized or if the slave ID is invalid.
+
+
+SEE ALSO
+--------
+linkmb:modbus_set_slave[3]
+
+AUTHORS
+-------
+The libmodbus documentation was written by Stéphane Raimbault
+<stephane.raimbault@gmail.com>
